# Code Quality Standards

## Single Responsibility
- Each function does one thing
- Each module owns one domain
- Break complex functions into named helpers

## Error Handling
- Validate inputs at system boundaries (user input, external APIs)
- Use try/catch for async operations
- Return specific error types, not generic `Error`

## Naming
- Function names describe what they do: `processOrderPayment` not `handle`
- Boolean variables start with `is`, `has`, `can`: `isAuthenticated`
- Constants in SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE

## Comments
- Add comments only when logic is non-obvious
- Prefer descriptive function names over explanatory comments
- Document the WHY, not the WHAT

## Avoid
- Nested callbacks / callback hell
- Magic numbers (use named constants)
- Premature abstraction (three similar lines beat a premature helper)
- Feature flags for one-time code

## Testing
- Write tests before implementation (TDD)
- Test behavior, not implementation details
- Use `test.each()` / `@pytest.mark.parametrize` for repetitive cases
- Cover: happy path, null/empty, boundaries, error cases
